A yet-to-be identified 25-year-old man, is dead after drowning in a river at Zangon Buhari in Bunkere Local Government Area of Kano State on Tuesday, September 15,2020. According to the Public Relations Officer , Kano State Fire Service, Saidu Mohammed, the deceased was said to have gone to bath in the river when he unfortunately drowned.“We received a distress call from Zangon Buhari in Bunkure local government at 06:30 am hours.In response to the call we sent our rescue team with equipments to the scene of incident and discovered it was a man of about 25 years drowned into a pond.The victim was pulled out unconscious and confirmed dead. His corpse was handed over to ward head of Zangon Buhari on behalf of his families,” He said. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.